Class AdobePSDCompositeMutableBranch

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePSDCompositeBranch
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobePSDCompositeMutableBranch

  • public class AdobePSDCompositeMutableBranch
extends AdobePSDCompositeBranch
    AdobePSDCompositeMutableBranch allows for changes to be made to the current PSD composite branch.

        Inserts the given layer at the given index position within the list of layers of parent.
        Parameters:
        layer - the layer node to be inserted.
        parent - the group layer what should become the new parent of the layer or null in order to insert the layer in the list of root layers.
        index - the index where to insert the layer node at.
        Returns:
        AdobePSDMutableLayerNode The updated layer node.
        Throws:
        com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.dcx.AdobeDCXException - If something goes wrong. Note: This method will modify the layer id of the layer node.

      • updatePixelsOf

        public AdobePSDMutableLayerNode updatePixelsOf(AdobePSDLayerNode layer,
                                               com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.psd.Point origin,
                                               java.lang.String sourceFile,
                                               boolean copy)
        Updates the pixels of the given layer node from sourceFile.
        Parameters:
        layer - the layer node to update. This must be a layer node of type AdobePSDLayerNodeTypeRGBPixels.
        origin - x and y offset of the pixels.
        sourceFile - the bitmap file. Must be a PNG file.
        copy - whether to copy or move source file.
        Returns:
        AdobePSDMutableLayerNode the updated layer node or null if something went wrong. Note: This method returns the modified layer node but doesn't modify the layer node that was passed in. If you want to make further changes to the layer node you will need to use the returned layer node to do so.

      • updateMaskOf

        public AdobePSDMutableLayerNode updateMaskOf(AdobePSDLayerNode layer,
                                             com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.psd.Point origin,
                                             java.lang.String sourceFile,
                                             boolean copy)
                                      throws com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.dcx.AdobeDCXException
        Updates or adds the mask of the given layer node from sourceFile.
        Parameters:
        layer - the layer node to update.
        origin - x and y offset of the mask.
        sourceFile - the bitmap file. Must be a PNG file.
        copy - whether to copy or move source file.
        Returns:
        AdobePSDMutableLayerNode the updated layer node or null if something went wrong.
        Throws:
        com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.dcx.AdobeDCXException - in case of a failure. Note: This method returns the modified layer node but doesn't modify the layer node that was passed in. If you want to make further changes to the layer node you will need to use the returned layer node to do so.

      • removeMaskOf

        public AdobePSDMutableLayerNode removeMaskOf(AdobePSDLayerNode layer)
                                      throws com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.dcx.AdobeDCXException
        Removes the layer mask of the given layer node. Is a no-op if the layer node doesn't have a mask.
        Parameters:
        layer - the layer node to remove the mask from.
        Returns:
        AdobePSDMutableLayerNode object representing the updated layer node. Null is returned if something went wrong.
        Throws:
        com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.adobeinternal.storage.dcx.AdobeDCXException - in case of a failure. Note: This method returns the modified layer node but doesn't modify the layer node that was passed in. If you want to make further changes to the layer node you will need to use the returned layer node to do so.
